Since then there's been a conscious effort in TN to avoid caste surnames. 

Instead they resorted to use father's name as surnames / initials. 

Later , in line with the feministic nature of Dravidian movement, mother's names too were included in surnames/ initials.

The first Tamil Provincial Self respect conference at Chengalpet in 1929 saw the passing of a resolution to abolish caste surnames. 

Periyar's took the oath as ' I E. Ve. Ramasamy Naicker would henceforth be known as E. Ve. Ramasamy.'
